'''Plumpy'Nut''' is a sweetened peanut-based paste that starving children find palatable and easy to eat, enabling them to gain weight quickly. It is a mix of peanuts, sugar, vegetable oil and skimmed milk powder, enriched with vitamins and minerals). It is classed as a [[Ready-to-Use Therapeutic Food]].

The maker, Nutriset, protects its near-monopoly with patents, which is controversial. Some manufacturers of similar products, for example in Haiti, ignore the patents. 

